Helper:

```java
private void mockCallbackUntilTokenExchange(Map<String, Object> tokenResponse) {
    when(redisAuthTransactionService.findByState("state-123"))
            .thenReturn(authTransaction());
    when(partnerRepositoryClient.getApp("B2BOOST_BE"))
            .thenReturn(validAppConfig());
    when(oidcDiscoveryClient.loadMetadata("issuer-uri"))
            .thenReturn(metadata());
    when(oidcTokenService.exchangeToken(
            anyString(),
            anyString(),
            any(AppConfigResponse.class),
            any(AuthTransaction.class)
    )).thenReturn(tokenResponse);
}
```

Use this if you refactor token exchange out. That will give clean coverage and avoid painful `WebClient` chain mocking.
